Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.97,0:14:10.97,Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Over the Cuckoo's Nest
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.23,0:14:20.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}It's coming undone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.15,0:14:23.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Oh no, pulling it will make it worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.94,0:14:27.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}What should I do for something like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.09,0:14:50.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.43,0:14:51.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.40,0:15:06.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Waiting for me at that house of shogi...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.86,0:15:10.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...were the true children of the family, who also\Naspired to be professional shogi players.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.41,0:15:14.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}Don't be so full of yourself!\NYou're just a "zero"!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.50,0:15:19.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kyouko, the daughter,\Nfour years older than me,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.71,0:15:23.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and Ayumu, the son, a third-grader\Nwho was the same age as me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.64,0:15:40.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dear, please forgive her. She's had enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.98,0:15:43.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,- No.\N- Kyouko is a girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.69,0:15:47.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't just about shogi.\NHow dare she strike an opponent after losing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.82,0:15:49.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.53,0:15:51.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Father was strict with Kyouko.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.03,0:15:58.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I think he was harder on her\Nbecause of her strength.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.41,0:16:02.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She was as tempestuous as a storm\Nin every respect.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.34,0:16:07.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Her shogi style, her disposition,\Nand her beauty, too.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.72,0:16:11.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. What are you staring at, twerp?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.52,0:16:18.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Knock it off! Kyouko!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.64,0:16:22.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Um, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.10,0:16:24.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Would you like some more?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.11,0:16:26.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.32,0:16:30.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what was that just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.78,0:16:33.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean, "Dad"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.20,0:16:36.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.66,0:16:39.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is it strange? I told him to call me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.66,0:16:42.54,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Why? That boy is an apprentice, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.54,0:16:44.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}You didn't adopt him,\Nso why would he call you "Dad"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.34,0:16:48.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't relax\Nif he called me "Master" in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.76,0:16:52.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you think of me\Nas being his "shogi father"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.18,0:16:55.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That reminds me,\NMr. Inoue from the training hall told me, Rei.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.89,0:17:00.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He said you beat Mr. Hashimoto,\Nthe famous amateur. That's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.90,0:17:13.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}Father loved shogi.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.82,0:17:17.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}Good or bad,\Neverything was centered around shogi for him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.04,0:17:24.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Therefore, those who loved him\Nhad no choice but to get stronger...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.71,0:17:27.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}{\i1}I had a question\Nabout losing entrance into the league...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.88,0:17:30.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...in order to stay in his field of vision.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.05,0:17:36.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And then...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.01,0:17:40.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...Ayumu was the first one\Nto have a breakdown.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.89,0:17:43.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ayumu seems to be\Nin low spirits at school lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.10,0:17:48.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His grades are dropping, too.\NHas something happened at home?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.52,0:17:54.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well, the apprentice we've taken in\Nhas surpassed him at shogi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.07,0:18:00.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm quitting shogi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.54,0:18:03.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.79,0:18:07.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he won't continue\Nunless someone persuades him, it's pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.33,0:18:08.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.17,0:18:13.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If he isn't someone who can convince himself\Nand make progress on his own, it's pointless.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.38,0:18:17.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Becoming a professional isn't the goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.22,0:18:22.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The path after becoming that\Nwill make your head spin.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.18,0:18:27.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The further you go, the steeper it becomes,\Nand there won't be anyone around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.69,0:18:33.65,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Only someone who can maintain himself\Nwill continue to make progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.40,0:19:18.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! Why do I have to quit the federation?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.24,0:19:21.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you can't beat Rei,\Nthere's no point in going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.99,0:19:24.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you make it to the 1st dan,\Nthere'll be stronger players everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.12,0:19:29.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You understand, right, Kyouko?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.17,0:19:34.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So in the end,\Nonly someone else's kid made the cut?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.50,0:19:36.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's Kiriyama's son, right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.59,0:19:41.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So he went out of his way to raise his\Nrival's child, who then upstaged his own kids.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.14,0:19:42.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How ironic.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.53,0:19:59.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After that, Kyouko spent a lot of time\Ngallivanting around town,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.40,0:20:02.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}while Ayumu shut himself in his room\Nand became immersed in video games.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.62,0:20:05.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The three of us no longer spent time together.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.66,0:20:10.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I couldn't bear the situation, so I became\Nincreasingly absorbed in shogi. And then...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.88,0:20:16.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}By the end of my second year in middle school,\Nand one step away from being a professional,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.80,0:20:19.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I had reached the 3rd dan league.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.63,0:20:24.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There is a species of bird\Nthat does not raise its own children,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.55,0:20:26.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but engages in "brood parasitism."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.93,0:20:31.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The cuckoo lays its eggs\Nin the nests of shrikes or meadow buntings.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.60,0:20:37.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The hatched chick then tosses the original eggs\Nout of the nest before they're hatched.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.11,0:20:41.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In this way, it takes over the nest.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.40,0:20:45.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When the parents return, none the wiser,\Nthey work hard to feed and raise{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.91,0:20:48.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the chicks of the bird\Nthat murdered their own offspring.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.91,0:20:50.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ah, that's me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.29,0:20:55.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if the cuckoo chick\Noutgrows its surrogate parents,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.42,0:20:58.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}they will continue to feed their chick.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.38,0:21:01.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That bird is me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.05,0:21:04.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're really not going to high school?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.26,0:21:06.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.47,0:21:08.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure that's what you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.85,0:21:14.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I think school is a place you go to\Nin order to choose your future course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.73,0:21:17.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,So I don't think it's necessary for me anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.69,0:21:22.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If I continue at this rate, this year,\Nor if that proves impossible,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.24,0:21:26.20,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,next year, I'll surpass the 3rd dan league\Nand become a professional.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.33,0:21:29.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to focus on shogi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.83,0:21:33.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After I become a professional,\NI'll do my best to improve my performance,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.92,0:21:35.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll leave that house.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.63,0:21:38.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,win tournaments and money,\Nand save that money...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.59,0:21:40.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I have to leave there as soon as possible.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.96,0:21:42.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so I can become independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.64,0:21:48.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Before I devour the members of that family...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.51,0:21:51.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...and Father as well.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.23,0:21:54.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.86,0:21:59.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little zig-zaggy...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.40,0:22:03.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,...but it'll be okay.\NIt won't come undone anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.91,0:22:09.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Good. I can still wear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.41,0:22:12.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Rei? Are you cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.41,0:22:14.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm the cuckoo...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.29,0:22:18.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know. For now, put this on.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.38,0:22:19.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry it's mine...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.88,0:22:23.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...standing over the lives\Nthat were thrust aside.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.26,0:22:25.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's a little big on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.76,0:22:28.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's okay. I'm happy to wear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.30,0:22:31.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's really warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.31,0:22:35.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I hear them calling out a song of spring.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.52,0:22:40.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Thank you, Dad.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.69,0:22:45.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I think, that if I truly were a bird,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.36,0:22:47.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}then at least...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.41,0:22:53.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I could have never known\Nabout this relentless pain.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.04,0:23:00.04,Next Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Over the Cuckoo's Nest
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.01,0:24:32.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Next Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.01,0:24:36.97,EpNum,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 6
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.34,0:24:33.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.68,0:24:38.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Chinatown! In Yokohama.\NWe can get meat dumplings, or chili shrimp.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.27,0:24:42.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,How about a place with a beautiful beach,\Nwhere we can relax?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.02,0:24:45.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Digging for sweet potatoes!\NAnd a soy sauce factory!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.52,0:24:50.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's soft-pedal it, and talk about it\Nmore indirectly. That's too straightforward.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.11,0:24:54.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"March... March Comes in Like a Lion".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.16,0:24:58.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Momo likes Bodoro more than lions!
